# Environment Configuration

Replace the values below with your actual configuration.

## Backend Configuration

### API Port
```
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
```

### File Upload Settings
```
MAX_FILE_SIZE=10485760  # 10MB in bytes
UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads
```

### WhatsApp Configuration
```
WHATSAPP_NUMBER=7349757596
```

## Frontend Configuration

### Client API Base URL
```
API_BASE=http://localhost:5000/api
```

### Admin API Base URL
```
API_BASE=http://localhost:5000/api
```

## Database (for future use)

When migrating to MongoDB or another database:

```
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=27017
DB_NAME=suvini_clothing
DB_USER=admin
DB_PASSWORD=password
```

## CORS Settings

Current CORS configuration allows all origins. For production, restrict to:

```
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://yourdomain.com,https://admin.yourdomain.com
```

## File Paths

```
CLOTHES_DB=./data/clothes.json
WISHLIST_DB=./data/wishlist.json
UPLOADS_DIR=./uploads
```

## Deployment Settings

### Production Backend URL
```
API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
```

### Production Client URL
```
CLIENT_URL=https://yourdomain.com
```

### Production Admin URL
```
ADMIN_URL=https://admin.yourdomain.com
```

---

**Note:** Keep sensitive information in environment variables, not in code.
